<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Delcassé</persName>,
                                minister for foreign affairs, to Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-14"><hi rend="italic">September 14,
                                    1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I beg your excellency to accept the sincere and keen condolences of the
                            French nation and Government, who share with all their hearts in the
                            mourning of the nation and Government of the United States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Delcassé</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>